(119, 833, 'News - Test Module Template	', 'news-test-module-template', '[mb2pb_section section_tab_cend="" section_tab_advaced_end="" id="" section_tab_advanced_start="" section_tab_video_end="" video_stoponblur="1" video_autoplay="1" video_loop="1" video_quality="default" video_id="" section_tab_video_start="" section_tab_parallax_end="" parallax_speed="0.25" parallax="0" section_tab_parallax_start="" section_tab_style_end="" class="" section_stylespacer2="" bg_attachment="scroll" bg_csize="" bg_size="cover" bg_cposition="" bg_position="0 0" bg_repeat="no-repeat" bg_image="" bg_color="" color_scheme="light" section_tab_style="" asection_tab_general_end="" admin_label="Section" padding_bt="0" padding_tp="0" section_tab_general="" section_tab_cstart="" section_tab_list=""][mb2pb_row row_tab_cend="" row_tab_video_end="" video_stoponblur="1" video_autoplay="1" video_loop="1" video_quality="default" video_id="" row_tab_video_start="" row_tab_parallax_end="" parallax_speed="0.25" parallax="0" row_tab_parallax_start="" row_tab_style_end="" class="" row_stylespacer2="" bg_attachment="scroll" bg_size="cover" bg_position="0 0" bg_repeat="no-repeat" bg_image="" bg_color="" color_scheme="light" row_tab_style="" arow_tab_general_end="" admin_label="Row" padding_bt="0" padding_tp="0" column_hpadding="normal" cwidth="" layout="0" row_tab_general="" row_tab_cstart="" row_tab_list=""][mb2pb_col class="mb2pb-column col-sm-6 cnoempty" row_tab_list="" col_tab_cstart="" col_tab_style="" padding_tp="0" padding_bt="0" color_scheme="light" custom_class="" col_tab_style_end="" col_tab_bg="" bg_color="" bg_image="" bg_repeat="no-repeat" bg_position="0 0" bg_size="cover" col_tab_bg_end="" col_tab_cend=""][mb2pb_text title="" titletag="h4" width="" position="left" margin="" padding="" bg_color="" gradient="0" class="" admin_label=""]<p>The template shows the systematic construct of a Test Module. Following the template is an example of a complete Test Module and the step-by-step sequence of ABT test development.</p>\r\n<p>Each Test Module is given a descriptive name to make it easy to identify what the tests in the module cover.</p>\r\n<p>There are four sections to a Test Module: Objectives, Initial, Test Case and Final.</p>\r\n<p>The OBJECTIVES section lists every objective associated with the module’s test cases and defines the scope of the test module. Objectives allow readers to understand why test cases are designed the way they are, and give an auditor a quick insight into the correctness and completeness of a test.</p>\r\n<p>The INITIAL section contains the action lines required for initialization of the\\ test. For example, actions for launching the application under test would be written here. This avoids repetitive steps when initialization is required for multiple test cases in the module.</p>\r\n<p>The TEST CASE section is where test cases are created. Each test case has a representative number, accompanied by title and one or more test objective lines. The title and objective explain the test case purpose.</p>\r\n<p>The FINAL section is for any cleanup operation upon test completion, such as closing the application under test.</p>[/mb2pb_text][/mb2pb_col][mb2pb_col class="mb2pb-column col-sm-6 cnoempty"][mb2pb_text title="" titletag="h4" width="" position="left" margin="" padding="" bg_color="" gradient="0" class="" admin_label=""]The Test Module template and example is available for download.[/mb2pb_text][mb2pb_button link="#" target="" type="primary" size="" fw="0" icon="" title="" ttpos="top" rounded="0" margin="" class="ta-button" admin_label=""]Download[/mb2pb_button][mb2pb_image url="images/news/testmodule-1.png" align="" width="" height="" crop="0" link="" video_id="" lightbox="0" margin="" class="" alt="" admin_label=""][/mb2pb_image][/mb2pb_col][/mb2pb_row][/mb2pb_section]', '', -2, 2, '2017-03-23 09:39:43', 816, '', '2017-03-23 09:39:43', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-03-23 09:39:43', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"